'''Tidjikja''' ({{Lang-ar|ØªØ¬ÙØ¬Ø©}}) is the capital of the [[Tagant]] region of central [[Mauritania]], lying on the [[Tagant plateau]]. Founded in 1680, it has a population of around 6,000 people.
The town is known for its [[palm tree]]s and its [[vernacular architecture]]. The town is also home to an [[airport]].
Nearby towns and villages include [[Moudjeria]] (65.8&nbsp;nm), [[Ksar el Barka]] (46.4&nbsp;nm), [[Rachid]] (21.3&nbsp;nm), [[Ksar el Khali]] (143.4&nbsp;nm), [[Ouadane]] (143.4&nbsp;nm), [[Boumdeit]] (67.1&nbsp;nm) and [[Serotandi]] (46.0&nbsp;nm) .
